HOUSE RESOLUTION 46
By Parkinson
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Jimmy Taylor, Jr.
WHEREAS, we were greatly saddened to learn of the passing of Jimmy Taylor, Jr.; and
WHEREAS, Jimmy Taylor was an exemplary public servant and consummate
professional who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for his fellow citizens in
numerous capacities; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Taylor was a respected businessman and entrepreneur, having owned
a tiling business and a cleaning service; and
WHEREAS, a gentleman of many talents and interests, Jimmy Taylor was a founding
member of the choir "The Covenant Keepers," and in addition to his position as a licensed
minister, he was a skilled singer, songwriter, and musician; and
WHEREAS, deeply devoted to his family, Mr. Taylor always endeavored to remain true
to family values of the highest order and was most proud of his role as a doting father, husband,
son, and brother; and
WHEREAS, Jimmy Taylor leaves behind an indelible legacy of integrity and probity in
public life, compassion and loyalty in private life, and diligence and dedication in all his chosen
endeavors; and
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should remember the bountiful life of this exceptional
public servant and human being; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we honor the
memory of Jimmy Taylor, Jr., reflecting fondly upon his impeccable character and his stalwart
commitment to living the examined life with courage and conviction.
